<subSubSection id="189D6519FFD779712936F9CFFB88D0F9" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="50383692FFD779712936F9CFFB88D0F9" blockId="6.[840,1478,1313,1956]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis id="62F3EA80FFD779712936F9CFFC21D047" bold="true" box="[863,1003,1569,1588]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="97874D11FFD779712E6AF9F1FB40D046" authorityName="S. Knapp" authorityYear="2010" box="[1027,1162,1567,1589]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sousae">
<emphasis id="62F3EA80FFD779712E6AF9F1FB40D046" box="[1027,1162,1567,1589]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Solanum sousae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from southern Mexico in the states of Puebla and Oaxaca, in mesophyllous forests and oak-pine- 
<taxonomicName id="97874D11FFD779712E7FF9B6FB4AD01E" box="[1046,1152,1624,1645]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Altingiaceae" genus="Liquidambar" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="62F3EA80FFD779712E7FF9B6FB4AD01E" box="[1046,1152,1624,1645]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Liquidambar</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
forests on steep slopes with rich soils, from 
<quantity id="977F9B77FFD7797129DDF99AFBF4D0F9" box="[948,1086,1652,1674]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="1.9" metricValueMin="1.6" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="m" value="1750.0" valueMax="1900.0" valueMin="1600.0">1600–1900 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="189D6519FFD779712936F97CFB42D088" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="50383692FFD779712936F97CFB42D088" blockId="6.[840,1478,1313,1956]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis id="62F3EA80FFD779712936F97CFC12D0D6" bold="true" box="[863,984,1682,1701]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Etymology.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="97874D11FFD779712999F97EFBB2D0D5" authorityName="S. Knapp" authorityYear="2010" box="[1008,1144,1680,1702]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sousae">
<emphasis id="62F3EA80FFD779712999F97EFBB2D0D5" box="[1008,1144,1680,1702]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Solanum sousae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is named in honour of Mario Sousa Sánchez (MEXU), whose dedication to the advance of knowledge of the Mexican flora has resulted in a whole new generation of Mexican botanists.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="189D6519FFD779712936F8ECFAE8D11F" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="50383692FFD779712936F8ECFAE8D11F" blockId="6.[840,1478,1313,1956]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis id="62F3EA80FFD779712936F8ECFB0CD165" bold="true" box="[863,1222,1794,1814]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Preliminary conservation status.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="97874D11FFD779712EB7F8EFFAA9D164" authorityName="S. Knapp" authorityYear="2010" box="[1246,1379,1793,1815]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sousae">
<emphasis id="62F3EA80FFD779712EB7F8EFFAA9D164" box="[1246,1379,1793,1815]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Solanum sousae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from only three widely dispersed collections, none of which falls within a protected area. It must be considered at threat, but further collecting and observation are a priority.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
